&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 12 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Staff Benefit Department is an ambitious service providing a range of administration services to all of the NHS Wales organisations.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for an administration assistant with NHS admin experience to fulfil the role of Benefit Scheme Admin Support Officer delivering high quality administration services to the organisations across NHS Wales.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a Benefit Scheme Admin Support Officer you will deliver a wide range of administration services for which you will be required to be confident with Microsoft Office. The post holder will ideally have a range of administration knowledge.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will be emailed and interviews will take place virtually.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Jones - Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;claire.a.jones@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
